						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Jaṭāvarmaṉ Kulaśēkhara. Year 2: A.D. 1192.</hi></p>						

						<p>(<hi rend="italic">Mithuna, śu.</hi>, 13, Wednesday, <hi rend="italic">Anila</hi> = A.D. 1192, May 27, Wednesday.).</p>						

						<p>Gift of half <hi rend="italic">vēli</hi> of land by the assembly of Chōḷāntakachaturvēdimaṅgalam, a <hi rend="italic">brahmadēya</hi> in Pāgaṉūr-kūṟṟam to the mendicants <hi rend="italic">(paricārakar)</hi> of the <hi rend="italic">Yōgasthāna</hi> of Kaṟṟavar-dāsar, situated in the village. The grant was resolved by the <hi rend="italic">mahājanas, bhaṭṭas</hi> and managers of the village, in a meeting held at the Vīrapāṇḍiyaṉ hall and the tax, <hi rend="italic">sabhāviṉiyōgam</hi> on the land was also exempted. The long list of signatories of village functionaries included two accountants and two sculptors <hi rend="italic">(silpāchāris)</hi>, the latter members engraved the inscription.</p>						

						</summary>
